$ Shell command: modprobe
@ modprobe

`modprobe` adds or removes → Linux/kernel/module[kernel modules] to/from the → Linux/kernel.

{ TODO

  { modprobe #modprobe-parse

    When `→ Linux/shell/commands/modprobe` loads a module, it parses `→ Linux/fhs/proc/cmdline` to collect module parameters for the module being loaded.

  }
